# Q.1: Plot and observe the statistical distribution of the magnitude of earthquakes.
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.histplot(earthquake_data['magnitude'], kde=True, color='skyblue')
plt.title('Distribution of Earthquake Magnitudes')
plt.xlabel('Magnitude')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.show()

#Q.2: Plot and interpret the observations of the changes of earthquake magnitude with respect to month.


# Assuming you have a 'Date' column in your dataset, convert it to datetime format.

earthquake_data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(earthquake_data['date_time'], dayfirst=True)
In [7]:
# Extract month from the 'Date' column

earthquake_data['Month'] = earthquake_data['Date'].dt.month
In [8]:
# Create a bar plot to observe the changes in magnitude with respect to month
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x='Month', y='magnitude', data=earthquake_data, errorbar=None)
plt.title('Earthquake Magnitude Changes with Respect to Month')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Mean Magnitude')
plt.show()
